cs.CV, cs.GR, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.MM 

This paper deals with computer vision techniques for estimating outdoor illumination from a single low dynamic range image. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). The paper also involves graphics techniques for rendering photorealistic virtual objects, which suggests that it could also belong to cs.GR (Computer Graphics). The use of a CNN for training and inference suggests that it could belong to cs.LG (Machine Learning), and the use of a physically-based illumination model suggests that it could belong to cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). Finally, the use of HDR environment maps suggests that it could belong to cs.MM (Multimedia).
